{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/336/comments/2994617.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/336#comment-2994617"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/336.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 336, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "ability to specify \"unassembled\" model by adding joint offsets for both parent and child link"}, "content": {"raw": "Possible alternative, somewhat more compact:\n\n```\n#!xml\n<joint name=\"joint1\" type=\"revolute\">\n  <parent link=\"link1\">\n    <pose>0 0 1 0 0 0</pose>\n  </parent>\n  <child link=\"link2\">\n    <pose>0 0 1 0 0 0</pose>\n  </child>\n  ...\n</joint>\n\n```\nOr could use 'name' rather then 'link' as the attribute. Link seems clearer though.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Possible alternative, somewhat more compact:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-xml\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"nt\">&lt;joint</span> <span class=\"na\">name=</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;joint1&quot;</span> <span class=\"na\">type=</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;revolute&quot;</span><span class=\"nt\">&gt;</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">&lt;parent</span> <span class=\"na\">link=</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;link1&quot;</span><span class=\"nt\">&gt;</span>\n    <span class=\"nt\">&lt;pose&gt;</span>0 0 1 0 0 0<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/pose&gt;</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">&lt;/parent&gt;</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">&lt;child</span> <span class=\"na\">link=</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;link2&quot;</span><span class=\"nt\">&gt;</span>\n    <span class=\"nt\">&lt;pose&gt;</span>0 0 1 0 0 0<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/pose&gt;</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">&lt;/child&gt;</span>\n  ...\n<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/joint&gt;</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>Or could use 'name' rather then 'link' as the attribute. Link seems clearer though.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2013-01-30T22:06:59.093258+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Sherman", "uuid": "{997c6f1e-e2a3-4f0e-8fa4-fed745840d50}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B997c6f1e-e2a3-4f0e-8fa4-fed745840d50%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B997c6f1e-e2a3-4f0e-8fa4-fed745840d50%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/355dea43ed612b7be3c9361df2d52213d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsMS-2.png"}}, "nickname": "sherm1", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:4590c319-b75f-4187-93d4-6cec61da74f7"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 2994617}